            "answer_text": "Absolutely.  In fact, it's a given that every four years, on election day, one of the almost mandatory camera shots of the election will be the current President casting their ballot, generally \"back home\" where they lived before becoming President (Washington DC is considered a temporary home for the President, so they are not obligated to switch registrations). Likewise, you will see a shot of the candidates in the race (if the President is not running for reelection) casting their ballots at their home precinct, surrounded by cameras, before (traditionally) retreating to their Headquarters to monitor the results as they come in. ",
